00:00:03.290 --> 00:00:09.650
 To prepare a good gazpacho you need: 100 ml of olive oil, 1 kg of ripe tomatoes, 

00:00:09.650 --> 00:00:16.550
 30 ml of vinegar preferably from Jerez, 1 clove of garlic, 150 g. hard white bread, 

00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:23.470
 1 green pepper, 1 cucumber, a small onion and 2 pinches of salt and if you wish 

00:00:23.470 --> 00:00:28.290
 for garnishing dices of cucumber, green pepper, etc ... 

00:00:28.290 --> 00:00:36.000
 After washing the tomatoes, cut them and put them in a large bowl 

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.490
 Then let the bread soak for a few minutes in a little water to soften it 

00:00:40.490 --> 00:00:42.760
 Peel the cucumber Cut and pour into the bowl 

00:00:42.760 --> 00:00:51.030
 Wash and seed the green pepper cut and add in the bowl 

00:00:51.030 --> 00:00:56.340
 Peel onion Cut into small pieces 

00:00:56.340 --> 00:01:08.130
 Peel the clove of garlic, cut in half to remove the central stem and put in 

00:01:08.130 --> 00:01:16.370
 the bowl Now add the bread 

00:01:16.370 --> 00:01:19.940
 The oil and the vinagre 

00:01:19.940 --> 00:01:27.380
 Add 2 good pinches of salt and add to the bowl 

00:01:27.380 --> 00:01:36.420
 Mix everything well Feel free to taste and rectify 

00:01:36.420 --> 00:01:41.740
 seasoning if necessary Reserve in fridge and serve fresh with as 

00:01:41.740 --> 00:01:48.020
 accompaniment if you wish dice of cucumber, green pepper, etc ... 

00:01:48.020 --> 00:01:51.900
 The Mediterranean flavor of gaspacho will transport you to Spain! 

